The paper focuses on multi-task learning (MTL) for natural language processing (NLP) tasks, specifically sequence tagging. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also extensively discusses empirical results and experiments, indicating a focus on machine learning, which suggests cs.LG (Machine Learning) as the second most likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of embeddings, which is a common technique in both cs.CL and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also discusses the clustering of tasks, which could potentially fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) or cs.CV (Computer Vision) sub-categories.
